The paper focuses on image retrieval, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of Deep Neural Networks (DNN) for learning high-level image representation is a common technique in computer vision and machine learning, which suggests that the paper could also belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also mentions the use of clickthrough data for training, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
